OJEU Ref - 2017/S 159-328392

CPV Codes - 

33000000, 33100000, 33172000, 33172100, 33172200, 33170000

NHS Supply Chain seeks to establish a non-exclusive Framework Agreement for the supply to the NHS
Supply Chain customer base via the direct route of supply of;
- Anaesthesia Machines and related accessories (products and / or services);
- Ventilator Equipment and related accessories (products and / or services);
The term 'related accessories' refers to any options or accessories (Goods or Services) as relevant to the, said,types of equipment (or machines) that are supplied as standard and that enable the equipment (or machine)to operate immediately upon delivery. For example software modules, trolleys, cables, point of sale (POS)maintenance and after-sales warranty services.
The scope of this tender, and any resulting Framework Agreement, does not include the supply of consumable products only.

The project comprises of: 
(i) the erection of a suitable and approved access scaffolding system, removal and disposal of existing defective roof coverings and replacement with new roof coverings in strict accordance with the manufacturer's specification and warranty provisions;	
(ii) all associated builders work and repairs, including plumbing, brickwork and electrics as appropriate.

NHS England's plan to double access to IPS for people with severe and enduring mental illness by 20/21 presents the opportunity for a delivery partner to co-ordinate a response to the key implementation challenges and opportunities presented by the expansion.
Initially this project would be for 1 year to support the expansion with the potential to extend to support years 2 and 3.
We envisage the supplier's role to be:
a. Ensuring hands-on implementation support from a network of IPS consultants, in line with all successful implementation practice of IPS in other countries such as the US, Australia, and New Zealand;
b. Producing a workforce development programme to support recruitment and training of IPS staff;
c. Ensuring central resources for commissioners, IPS providers, and clinical teams are in place;
d. Providing effective reporting, monitoring, and evaluation mechanisms, to be used by services.
The provider would need to be able to operate across various locations nationwide in line with expansion plans.

This exercise is currently exploratory and the authorities reserve the right not to run the procurement.  

A market engagement session is being held on 9th March 2018 at 1400 hrs (GMT). Please email nhsengland.commercial@nhs.net if you would like to join the conference and joining details will be sent out to you.
